        " \"نَعَمْ وَ لَكِنْ لاَ يَتَعَمَّدْ قَطْعَ رَأْسِهِ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4172 - Hammad narrated from Al-Halabi, from Abu Abdillah (as), that he was asked about a man who slaughtered a bird and severed its head.\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, it may be eaten, but he should not deliberately cut off its head.\""
        ]
      }
